text.section:
Before calling and announcing a referendum, the certified agency shall determine and publicly announce through the public press at least 60 days before the date determined for the referendum:
The date, hours, polling places, and rules and regulations for voting;
The amount and basis of the assessment proposed to be collected;
The method by which the authorized assessment shall be collected; and
How the proceeds shall be administered and the general purposes to which they shall be applied.
